Global warming has changed food production patterns. Poverty still runs deep in Africa, with a third of the continent’s population still trapped in extreme penury. Kenya’s two-year tenure as a non-permanent member of the United Nations Security Council officially kicked off with the installation of the country’s flag at the UN headquarters on Monday January 4, 2020.
The ceremony also unfolded during Kenya’s final year as a member of the Peace and Security Council of the African Union. Kenya is joining four other new entrants to the most powerful UN organ at a time of heightened vulnerabilities to peace and security around the world, due to the Covid-19 pandemic.



