Nairobi now embodies the aspirations of not just African countries but also the larger global South; whose socioeconomic transformation prospects have been held back by conflict and intractable fragilities.
In Africa, many countries have been infiltrated by armed groups whose activities threaten lives and property. The threat of terrorism is another reality that many countries around the world, including Kenya, have to contend with.



