Beyond these national security concerns, there is a growing toll on human security in which climate change, global inequality and lately, pandemics are some of the key instigators.
Poverty
Global warming has changed food production patterns for millions of people. Poverty still runs deep in Africa, with a third of the continent’s population still trapped in extreme penury. The Covid-19 pandemic has only exacerbated the economic situation for many people across the world – making economic recovery and reconstruction a key anchor of global wellness.
These two strands of conflict have persisted around the world despite efforts multilateral efforts to stem them.
New approaches to conflict resolution and peace fortification must now be part of the broader engagements by concerned parties.



