The alternative is widespread hopelessness among the youth, making them amenable to conflict, crime and violent extremism.
Given the trans-boundary nature of the most debilitating challenges facing humanity today, it is only prudent that Kenya has identified multilateralism and global cooperation as the most effective vehicle to confront the challenges.
Countries, big and small, should commit to pool together ideas and resources while pulling in the same direction.
In a region fraught with conflicts, Nairobi has cut itself a profile of a peaceful country anchored on rule of law and democracy. Kenya has equally been active in negotiating peaceful resolutions of a number of conflicts in the continent while remaining an influential political actor in the region and continent.
The UNSC seat is another opportunity for Kenya to share its resourcefulness in creating a safer, peaceful and more prosperous world.
